genresAdvancedInfo.name: polish experimental electronic
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Polish experimental electronic music is a subgenre of experimental music that incorporates electronic instruments and technology to create new and unique sounds. It often features complex rhythms, glitchy textures, and abstract soundscapes, and is known for pushing the boundaries of what is possible in electronic music.
